1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE
RESOLUTION 1056 By: Munson
4
5
6
7 AS INTRODUCED
8 A Resolution proclaiming the month of April as Sexual
Assault Awareness Month and declaring Wednesday,
9 April 29, 2026, as Denim Day.
10
11
12 WHEREAS, the United States Government has declared April as
13 Sexual Assault Awareness Month and the nonprofit organizations Peace
14 Over Violence and the Young Women's Christian Association have
15 declared April 29, 2026, as Denim Day; and
16 WHEREAS, both events are intended to draw attention to the fact
17 that sexual violence remains a serious issue in our society; and
18 WHEREAS, sexual violence has a profound and lasting impact on
19 individuals, families, and communities, affecting people of all
20 ages, races, national origins, faiths, gender identities, sexual
21 orientations, immigration statuses, and economic backgrounds; and
22 WHEREAS, Sexual Assault Awareness Month and Denim Day were also
23 instituted to call attention to misconceptions and misinformation
24 about sexual violence and the problem that many people in our
Req. No. 17557 Page 1

1 soci ety remain disturbingly uninformed with respect to issues of
2 sexual harassment, assault, abuse, and rape; and
3 WHEREAS, national data indicate that one in three women and one
4 in four men will experience some form of sexual violence during
5 their lifetime, with even higher rates reported among people of
6 color, individuals with intellectual disabilities, and members of
7 underserved communities; and
8 WHEREAS, every sixty-eight seconds, somewhere in America,
9 someone is sexually assaulted, and every nine minutes, that victim
10 is a child; and
11 WHEREAS, one in three female victims of completed or attempted
12 rape experienced it for the first time between the ages of eleven
13 and seventeen; and
14 WHEREAS, in 2022, the State of Oklahoma ranked eighth in the
15 United States for rape rates, with approximately 4,500 sexual
16 assault cases in 2021; and
17 WHEREAS, workplace harassment is part of this issue, with one in
18 seven women leaving jobs due to sexual harassment; and
19 WHEREAS, with the support of compassionate community networks
20 and dedicated victim service providers, survivors can begin to
21 process trauma and rebuild their lives in environments where they
22 are heard, respected, and supported; and
23 WHEREAS, collaboration among elected officials, faith leaders,
24 educators, businesses, service providers, and community members
Req. No. 17557 Page 2

1 stre ngthens pathways for survivors to access resources that promote
2 safety, healing, and justice; and
3 WHEREAS, members of the Oklahoma House of Representatives
4 strongly support the efforts of Peace Over Violence and the Young
5 Women's Christian Association of Oklahoma City to educate persons in
6 our state about the true impact of sexual harassment, abuse,
7 assault, and rape in Oklahoma.
8 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
9 OF THE 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
10 THAT the Oklahoma House of Representatives does hereby proclaim
11 the month of April as Sexual Assault Awareness Month.
12 THAT the Oklahoma House of Representatives does hereby designate
13 April 29, 2026, as Denim Day and urges everyone to wear jeans on
14 this day to help communicate the message that there is no excuse and
15 there is never an invitation to harass, abuse, assault or rape.
